track_notes: I parked in the large parking area next to the campsite.  No problem in mid March, but I dont know if there are any restrictions when the campsite is open. Head west through a gate on the old road and turn south before the river bridge on the obvious path that runs alongside the campsite.  Through another gate and then you start to follow the obvious stalkers path.  The continues down the glen until it starts to climb up to the right.  At NG92501609 the path forks, keep right and head up hill following the Lochaber way marker posts.  Continue to the loch above.  Choose  your route around the loch, I went round the west side.  Then it is a simple case of going due north up steep grassy slopes, avoiding small outcrops, until you reach the east ridge of the peak, just below the summit.  Turn left, west, to ascend the final few metres to the summit. Large cairn with amazing views.
